{"title":"Specialized Crux Alloy is Back, Now With D’Aluisio Smartweld","link":"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-crux-alloy-daluisio-smartweld/","date":1718121600000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike-header--1536x1152.jpeg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp full bike header\" /></p>\n<p>The alloy version of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-specialized-crux-goes-full-gas-on-gravel-racing-w-725g-frame-big-tires/\">Specialized Crux</a> is back, and it’s lighter than ever! The all-new Specialized Crux DSW mimics its carbon brethren and weighs only 1399 grams for a frameset. However, this Crux isn’t the same World Champion <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-crux-jumper-is-a-throwback-to-the-early-days-of-team-stumpjumper/\">Bunny Hopper </a>cyclocross steed that Zdeněk Štybar raced. It’s a gravel bike, and it’s the “lightest alloy gravel bike ever made.” </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-ramp-up-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Specialized Crux DSW </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re new or returning to the Specialized Crux, the latest iteration pivoted towards the gravel side of life, moving away from the cyclocross race machine of the past. The new Crux is still a cyclocross-able machine, but the geometry and slopping toptube say ‘gravel’. The newest Crux version was also deemed the lightest gravel bike ever, and now its alloy counterpart shares the crown. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp headtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-headtube--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>D’Aluisio Smartweld Construction </h3>\n\n\n\n<p><em>How did it get so light?</em> The design team at Specialized uses the same D’Aluisio Smartweld (DSW) you’ll find on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/updated-specialized-allez-affordable-road-bike/\">Allez sprint</a>. It’s an engineering process that uses hydroforming to match tube-to-tube joints for better, stronger welds. This type of construction produces a lighter frame, and it is claimed to be twice as durable as a traditional alloy frame. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW frame pieces\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Connecting the Pieces </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The DSW frames are assembled using a single-piece downtube and bottom bracket, identical to the construction of the Allez Sprint. This one-piece downtube and bottom bracket help stiffen the bike and pedaling response. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW frame pieces\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The seat tube and chainstays are then mated to the hydroformed one-piece downtube and bottom bracket using the Specialized D’Aluisio Smartweld welding process.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW frame pieces rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-pieces-rear--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Specialized says the D’Aluisio smart weld process is refined, eliminating the need to overbuild tubes and welds. The yield is a 1399g alloy frame alone, but it also brings better ride quality and responsiveness. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"9504\" height=\"6336\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full-.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW frame set full\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full-.jpg 9504w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frame-set-full--768x512.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Frame Details </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Crux DSW keeps its weight down with help from a full carbon Fact12r Crux fork, like the carbon Crux versions. It has a threaded bottom bracket and upgrades to a SRAM UDH rear derailleur hanger (unlike the current carbon Crux).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"9504\" height=\"6336\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset-.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW frameset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset-.jpg 9504w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-frameset--768x512.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame boasts mechanical and electronic shifting compatibility, with zero headtube routing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay-.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"9504\" height=\"6336\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay-.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW seatstay\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay-.jpg 9504w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-seatstay--768x512.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tube shapes are slightly round for seat stays, and the top tube is slightly triangular. This might scare away some soft-shouldered cyclocrossers, but don’t fear; the tube tappers are flat near the seat tube junction.    </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp down tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-down-tube--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Specialized claims a complete Crux DSW tips the scales at 20lbs (9.37g) in a 56cm in the lightest colorway, and we found that to be 100% true on our scales.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp experience\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-experience--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What type of riding is it for? </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Crux DSW has the exact geometry and tire clearance as its carbon counterpart—that’s up to 47mm on 700c wheels and up to 2.1″ on a 650b wheel. It’s basically the carbon Crux, only aluminum. It’s safe to say the new Crux DSW is a gravel bike that can take a beating.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp front derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-derailleur--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The jury is out on how stiff and compliant that ride will be. Judging from my time on the Crux in both cyclocross and gravel, my hopes are high. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1327\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp front wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-297x154.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-1536x796.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-120x62.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-768x398.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-front-wheel-2048x1061.jpg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Specialized)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ride Tuned For On and Off-Road </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Alloy gets a bad rap for being harsh off-road. But anyone who rides a well-crafted alloy frame will tell you thats not 100% true. It’s all about tube shapes and geometry. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-bars--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For the Crux D’Aluisio Smartweld, the slightly longer reach delivers better weight distribution, and the full carbon fork eats up trail chatter, same a mix of round tubes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-fork--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the carbon model, it should offer a stable ride with an “in the middle for gravel and cyclocross” 72mm of bottom-bracket drop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp full side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-side--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Specialized Crux DSW Models </strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Specialized Crux DSW is available in a complete or frame-only model. The frames arrive in super cool, playful colors like the alloy Crux of the past. The complete bike offers a competitively built gravel machine that is a solid option when pitted against the Crux carbon. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-crankset--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Crux DSW Comp arrives with an SRAM 12-speed Apex setup, an 11-44T cassette, and a 40T front chain ring. As built, the bike weighs 20 lbs, but most is in the wheels, seatpost, and alloy bars. The saddle is a base-level Specialized Power and a great do-it-all saddle.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp 3 bottles\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-3-bottles--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><br />(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, the spec is solid. The wheels, though slightly heavy for racing, are an excellent spec for gravel and exploration on the bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-full-bike--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Jordan Villella)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rims are 25mm internal and, paired with the Specialized Pathfinder Pro tires, offer an excellent footprint for traction and speed. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Specialized Crux DSW Specs </strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frame</strong>: Specialized E5 Premium Aluminum Disc frame D’Aluisio Smartweld Technology, hydroformed aluminum tubing, tapered head tube, threaded BB</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fork</strong>: FACT Carbon, 12x100mm thru-axle, flat-mount disc</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Handlebars</strong>: Specialized Adventure Gear, 118.9mm drop x 70mm reach x 12º flare</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stem</strong>: Specialized, 3D-forged alloy, 4-bolt, 7-degree rise</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Front brake</strong>: SRAM APEX, Hydraulic Disc</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear brake</strong>: SRAM APEX, Hydraulic Disc</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shift lever</strong>: SRAM APEX, 12sp</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear derailleur</strong>: SRAM APEX XPLR, Mechanical</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cassette</strong>: SRAM PG 1231, XPLR, 11-44</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crankset</strong>: SRAM APEX XPLR, 40t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Chainring</strong>: 40t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottom bracket</strong>: SRAM DUB BSA 68 Wide</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Chain</strong>: SRAM APEX 12S</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheels</strong>: DT G540, Centerlock Disc, Tubeless Ready, 25mm internal width </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tires</strong>: Pathfinder Pro 2BR, 700×38</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle</strong>: Body Geometry Power Sport, steel rails</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost</strong>: Alloy, 2-bolt Clamp, 12mm offset, 27.2mm, anti-corrosion hardware</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Total Weight</strong>: 9.37kg (20 lb, 10.5 oz) Size: 56cm</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Specialized Crux DSW comp BB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Specialized-Crux-DSW-comp-BB-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Specialized Crux DSW</strong> Pricing </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Crux DSW Comp: </strong>$2,600, €2,700, £2,300, AUD 4,000</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>DSW Frame:</strong> $1,700,  €1,650, £1,500, AUD 2,500</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Specialized Crux DSW is shipping now to retailers and customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Look For a Review</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We just received our review ride for the Specialized Crux DSW. Look for a review as we put it through the remainder of gravel season and into cyclocross. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-crux-alloy-daluisio-smartweld/\">Specialized Crux Alloy is Back, Now With D’Aluisio Smartweld</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"bd664dbae51c192c99ca57e4407a7f9b04ca0c52654cd6bcebec275158463059","category":"Cycling"}